<td>Disk IO activity graph. Colors defined in RGB hexadecimal. If scale is non-zero, it becomes the scale for the graph. The lower case L <q>-l</q> switch uses a logarithmic scale to make small numbers more visible. The lower case T <q>-t</q> switch enables temperature gradient to make the color values change depending on the amplitude of the activity. <p class='ex'>${diskiograph /dev/sda 10,120 555555 AAAAAA -l}</p></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td><a id='diskiograph_read'></a><a href='#diskiograph_read'>diskiograph_read</a><p class='ar'>[device] [height][,width] [gradient color 1] [gradient color 2] [scale] [-t] [-l]</p></td>
