<td>Executes a Lua function with and draws a graph. Expects result value to be any number, and by default will scale to show the full range. See also <a href='#lua_load'>lua_load</a> on how to load scripts. Takes the switch '-t' to use a temperature gradient, which makes the gradient values change depending on the amplitude of a particular graph value (try it and see). Conky puts <q>conky_</q> in front of the function_name to prevent accidental calls to the wrong function unless you put you place <q>conky_</q> in front of it yourself. <p class='ex'></p></td>
